        <p>Under current US regulatory frameworks, spot crypto ETFs are strictly prohibited from staking their underlying assets. Therefore, unlike holding Solana directly in a personal wallet and staking it for an annual 5-8% yield, a Solana ETF currently only tracks the raw price movement of the asset. You sacrifice the yield for the convenience of the ETF.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What are the fees associated with a Solana ETF?</summary>
        <p>Like all Exchange-Traded Funds, Solana ETFs charge an ongoing annual management fee, commonly referred to as an expense ratio. This fee is automatically and invisibly deducted from the fund's total assets over time. Depending on the intense competition between the specific fund providers (like BlackRock or Bitwise), these fees typically range between 0.20% and 1.50% per year.</p>
      </details>
